td.p:
Article 12 of Council Regulation (EC) No 1/2003 of 16 December 2002 on the implementation of the rules on competition laid down in Articles [101 and 102 TFEU] (
OJ 2003 L 1, p. 1
) provides:

The Commission Notice on immunity from fines and reduction of fines in cartel cases (
OJ 2002 C 45, p. 3
) (‘the 2002 Leniency Notice’) sets out the conditions under which undertakings cooperating with the Commission in an investigation it is carrying out into a cartel may be exempted from fines, or may be granted reductions in any fine which would otherwise have been imposed on them. Point 11(a) of that notice stipulates in that regard that the undertaking must cooperate fully, on a continuous basis and expeditiously throughout the Commission’s administrative procedure and provide the Commission with all evidence that comes into its possession or is available to it relating to the suspected infringement.

